==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Carbonize
<hw>Car"bon*ize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Carbonized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Carbonizing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>carboniser</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To convert (an animal or
vegetable substance) into a residue of carbon by the action of fire or
some corrosive agent; to char.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To impregnate or combine with carbon, as in making
steel by cementation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Carbonometer</ent>⟦br⟧
